items.preText:
Could be a crucial little spell of play here. Mustafizur returns.

Pranav: "If only Asif Ali was sent before Shadab. Could have been needing 122 of 22 overs, removing the disastrous knock of 4 in 24. Decisions making skills gotta improve at this level. C'mon why will you save Asif Ali for later. He is a full time batsman!"
items.text: and he creates a chance first ball! Only it's dropped. Back of a length, the cutter, leaves the batsman off the pitch as he attempts to steer to third man. Straightforward catch to the right of Liton behind the stumps. He goes one-handed, casually, and the ball bounces off his glove

items.preText: Harun: "Either "Fizz" or " Mash" should come on attack!!!!" -- Someone's heard you. Both are on in tandem now. Mashrafe from round the wicket to Imam.
items.text: shot! Jumps out of his crease, gets one angled into his hitting arc, full, and just clatters it over wide long-on. First six of the innings

items.preText: Hamza: "The problem isn't whether Shadab should have been sent before or after Asif Ali. The problem is that we need to make peace with the fact that Shadab and Nawaz are not genuine all-rounders. They are handy tail enders at most."

items.preText:
A man in at gully, perhaps to try and stop him from picking up singles to third man. And also a potential catcher.

Srikanth: "Lilton Das is a part time keeper.. We had similar situation when Dravid used to keep wickets. If u see yday's team India, if MSD got injured we had 4 backup wicket keepers in playing XI, full time DK plus part time Rahul, Rayudu and even Kedar. " -- Liton's definitely a proper keeper. I think he lost sight of the ball momentarily, and kind of grabbed at the ball with one hand.
